name: CNNetwork
description: Julia autodifferentiation and CNN library, highly optimized for one specific use-case.

context: |
  This is a Julia autodifferentiation and CNN library optimized for a specific neural network.
  The project includes:
  - clothesolver.jl and autodiff.jl (core library files, may have different versions)
  - test.ipynb (tests the intended neural network architecture for fashion item classification)
  - profiler.ipynb (performance profiling and optimization analysis)
  - Performance.md (file which explaines changes and their performance effect, this is read only)
  - Performance_ai.md (file for ai agents for them to explain their changes)
  
  Goals:
  - Maintain >85% accuracy on fashion item classification
  - Maximize learning speed and performance
  - Keep codebase minimal and focused

instructions: |
  - Write all code in Julia
  - Maintain existing project structure unless explicitly told otherwise
  - Prioritize performance and code brevity
  - Profile before optimizing (use profiler.ipynb)
  - Document any changes to the library interfaces

include:
  - "*.jl"
  - "*.ipynb"
  - "Performance_ai.md"
  - "Performance.md"

exclude:
  - ".ipynb_checkpoints/**"
  - "__pycache__/**"
  - "*.tmp"
